Step 1: Calculate ROE  
• ROE is computed as (Net Profit ÷ Ending Owner's Equity) × 100.  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,103,190.60.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Owner's Equity = 14,103,190.60.  
• ROE = (1,103,190.60 / 14,103,190.60) × 100 ≈ 7.83%.

Step 2: Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total liabilities are the difference between Total Assets and Total Owner's Equity.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets = 16,213,861.65 and Total Owner's Equity = 14,103,190.60.  
• Total Liabilities = 16,213,861.65 – 14,103,190.60 = 2,110,671.05.  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 2,110,671.05 / 16,213,861.65 ≈ 0.13.

Step 3: Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit Margin is calculated as (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,638,420.67 and Total Revenue = 5,813,420.67.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (2,638,420.67 / 5,813,420.67) × 100 ≈ 45.38%.

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "7.83%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.13",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.38%"
  }
}
